  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two independent laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed; the Test conditions factor is one gradation below the required level due to the single test-condition configuration used in the validation campaign. The intended use is restricted to non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs under quasi-static axial compression-bending loads as defined by ASTM F1717, for Class II spinal fixation device submissions. Scope, patient population, and loading envelope are fully described in the governing Claim and Requirement documents referenced by this assurance package.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/req/f1717-compression-bending-noncan-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/claim/fea-f1717-noncan-compression-bending-accuracy",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/model/pedicle-screw-fea-ensemble-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
