      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is a commercially validated FEA solver with documented QA procedures including regression test suites, version-controlled release notes, and ISO 9001 certification. FDA CDRH internal solver instance is subject to equivalent institutional QA controls. Required gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark problems including patch tests and manufactured-solution comparisons were executed for the element types used (SOLID186, CONTA174). Results are within accepted tolerances documented in the solver verification manual. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "A systematic mesh convergence study was performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod junction regions. Peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness converged to within 2.1% between the medium and fine meshes. Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error below 3% for all quantities of interest."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residuals were monitored and converged below 1e-6 for all load steps. Force and moment equilibrium checks confirmed global balance within 0.01%. No divergence events recorded across 11 model instances."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Model setup was independently reviewed by a second analyst following a documented checklist. Boundary conditions, material assignments, and contact definitions were verified against the analysis plan prior to execution. No use errors identified."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive models are appropriate for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) and UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates within the ASTM F1717 load range. Contact mechanics are represented with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Literature supports this model form for quasi-static spinal construct analysis."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for each lot of Ti-6Al-4V rod and screw material. Geometric inputs derived from calibrated CMM measurements of physical test specimens. Coefficient of friction characterised by coupon-level tribology testing. Input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo sampling across reported tolerance ranges."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled per ASTM F1717 protocol. Samples drawn from production lots with documented traceability. Sample size provides sufficient statistical power for mean stiffness and yield load comparison at 80% power."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single load angle (5 degrees from vertical) as specified by ASTM F1717. Although this represents the standard regulatory condition, only one test condition was evaluated, limiting the breadth of validation evidence. This factor is one gradation below the required level; the shortfall is accepted given the regulatory standardisation of the test protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions and geometry were matched to each physical specimen individually using specimen-specific CMM data and measured torque values. Correspondence between simulation inputs and experimental conditions verified by independent review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load predicted by FEA compared against experimental measurements using ASME V&V 40 validation metric (area validation metric). Mean absolute percentage error 4.7% for stiffness and 6.2% for yield load across N=11 specimens. Both within pre-specified acceptance thresholds of 10%."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load under compression-bending are the primary quantities of interest for regulatory assessment of non-cannulated pedicle screw mechanical performance per FDA guidance and ASTM F1717. These quantities are directly linked to the clinical decision regarding device structural adequacy."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities replicate the ASTM F1717 test configuration that constitutes the regulatory intended use. Device geometry, material, assembly torque, and loading mode in validation experiments are representative of the submission device and its intended clinical loading environment. High relevance confirmed."
    }
