    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed the required gradation for model risk level 3. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs required 3) is accepted on the basis that ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standardised test configuration for regulatory submissions and that all other validation evidence is strong. Overall simulation credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory claim regarding non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending performance.",
